<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="reg-brownie" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Basic Brownies</title>

  <p>
    Ingredients:
  </p>
  <tabular>
    <row>
      <cell><m>\frac{1}{2}</m> cup butter</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>1 cup sugar</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>2 eggs</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
    <cell>1 teaspoon vanilla extract</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell><m>\frac{1}{3}</m> cup cocoa powder</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell><m>\frac{1}{2}</m> cup flour</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell><m>\frac{1}{4}</m> teaspoon salt</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>Chocolate chips (one handful, optional)</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>1/4 teaspoon baking powder (optional)</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell></cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell></cell>
    </row>
  </tabular>

  <p>Instructions
    <ol>
      <li>
        <p>
          Grease and flour a 9" x 9" pan.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Melt butter in a large saucepan.  Remove from heat, and stir in sugar, eggs, and vanilla.  Beat in cocoa powder, flour, salt and baking powder.  Spread into prepared pan.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Bake, preheated, at <m>350^\circ</m> for 29 minutes without chocolate chips and 31 minutes with chocolate chips.  Do not overcook.  Yield:  16 brownies.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </p>

  <p>
    Notes:
    <ul>
      <li>
        <p>
          If using chocolate chips, make sure to push them into the batter to avoid burning.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Only use baking powder if you want them extra-cakey.  They are pretty cakey without the baking powder.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </p>
</section>